===============================
INBOXIQ - PROJECT SETUP GUIDE
===============================

Project Architecture:
Frontend (Next.js)
        ↓
FastAPI Backend
        ↓
Redis Queue
        ↓
Worker
        ↓
PostgreSQL Database


========================================
STEP 1: START POSTGRESQL
========================================

Make sure PostgreSQL service is running.

Database Name:
email_ai


========================================
STEP 2: START REDIS
========================================

Option 1: If Redis is installed locally

Run:
redis-server


Option 2: Using Docker

Run:
docker run -p 6379:6379 redis


========================================
STEP 3: START BACKEND
========================================

Open terminal:

cd backend

Activate virtual environment:

.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

Run backend server:

python -m uvicorn main:app --reload


Backend runs on:
http://127.0.0.1:8000


========================================
STEP 4: START WORKER
========================================

Open another terminal:

cd backend

Activate virtual environment:

.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

Run worker:

python worker.py


========================================
STEP 5: START FRONTEND
========================================

Open another terminal:

cd inboxiq-frontend

Install dependencies:

npm install

Run frontend:

npm run dev


Frontend runs on:
http://localhost:3000


========================================
STEP 6: TEST THE SYSTEM
========================================

Open:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

Use POST /webhook

Example JSON:

{
  "subject": "Refund charged twice",
  "body": "My payment was deducted two times."
}


